Use DataTypeLib::GetRuntimeDataType to query the correct const DataType*. Some datatypes need to be converted into runtime types.
E.g. "int" and "float" will be adjusted to the 32 or 64 types which the compiler defined for the current platform.
But also types based on Int or Float (such as Vector) have to be converted.
Classification of the attribute. This can be any of the given enum types.
Command info: database id which loaded this description.
True if the attribute should be overwritable for takes in the take system.
This attribute is set for a variadic port. A variadic port can be expanded a number of times.
This attribute sets the default number of ports of a variadic port.
contains an array of ids in case isvariadic is true.This value will be filled in programmatically.
Show why the element has warnings
Include export: comment to be added to the include export
Command info: True to prevent this attribute from exporting to the header file.
True if the string should be inherited to descriptions which include this description.
True if the string is optional and doesn't need to be translated.
Command info: namespace that generated that symbol.

Is only set if the attribute was included by another attribute.
Id - database id of the included object
Data - identifier of the include attribute
This value returns the original data type id which defined the attribute

Classification of this description. This can be any of the given enum types.
node - allowsto define a node which appears in the node editor.
The processor processes a description, for example to create a node from the description and add it to the nodes registry.
A port of this node for an image Url. This is used when an Url is dropped on the node, and for some image-related node commands.
Command info: include file to generate relative to the executable.

If this is set, the described entity won't show up in the UI.

Original reference string of the translated string at the time of the last translation.

Translated children strings. 
Each entry in the dictionary contains a Tuple<String, String>.

Default Classification of the attributes inserted under this group.
If set to something else than "none" objects inserted under this group will be changed to this classification.
Id of the ui to use to display this attribute.
Accept list for link fields. It's possible to use symbolic names like Obase, Ocamera.
Id of the group into which the attribute should be assigned
Condition which will be evaluated before displaying the value. If the term returns false the attribute will be hidden.
Condition which controls the enabling of the ui element. True to enable it.
Optional Id of the parent attribute. If given the ui will ident the attribute. If the parent contains it's own id the parent is foldable.
True to open the parent group by default
Command "preset": Preset id to define the key under which the presetmembers will be stored. E.g. "net.maxon.presets.colors"
Command "preset": A list of preset members to store under the preset id.

Allows to reorder the enum fields of the DATADESCRIPTIONPROPS.
The following options are available:
"---" - add a seperator
<<any id>> - add a specific id
registry#<<name>> - fill in all members of an extension point
# - fill in all other member not listed explicitly

True if strings of children of this attribute are optional and not 
requiried to translate.

If the attribute is a "command" it's possible to specify the appearance of 
the command as a button or menu

Context for the command. 
nodecore - command belongs to the NodesGraphInterface
nimbuscore - command belongs to the NimbusInterface (includes nodecore)
nodepresenter - command belongs to the NodePresenterInterface
nodegraphwidget - command belongs to the NodeGraphWidgetInterface
Icon Id of the icon that should be used the id can be a qualified name of a registered icon or a c4d icon id as number.
True if the group should be open by default.

Number of columns the group should support.

True if the attribute should be hidden when the object is displayed as inline object
True if the string should be a multiline text.
True if the minvalue and maxvalue are valid.

Defines the pattern for the default name
Special ids: 
assetid - the asset id of the node
uniquenumber - the unique number of the node.
{{any attribute}} - value of the attribute
examples:
{{assetid}}.{{uniquenumber}} -> Bitmap.1
{{url}} || {{assetid}}.{{uniquenumber}} -> app.png if url is given, otherwise Bitmap.1
IDs for the DataDictionary of Application::GetMachineInfo().you can get the values by calling machineInfo.Get(MACHINEINFO::USERNAME) iferr_return;
Computer name returned by the OS.
User name of the currently logged in user.
OS build number as integer value.
Unique OS identifier. This id allows to identify a machine. Each machine (even VMs) should have it's unique identifier.

Unique OS identifier source. This id allows to identify a machine. Each machine (even VMs) should have it's unique identifier.
NONE
TPM: WIN TPM module
UEFI: WIN Uefi
REGISTRY: WIN registry
CRYPTOGRAPHYID: WIN old cryptography id
CRYPTOGRAPHYID_FALLBACK: WIN blocked collision id -> cryptography id
SERIALKEY: OSX kIOPlatformSerialNumberKey
UUIDKEY: OSX kIOPlatformUUIDKey
Languages in order of preference. the first language is the most preferred language.
Number of threads including hyper threading cores.
